value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + oxaloacetate + propanoyl-CoA = (2R,3S)-2-methylcitrate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: butanoyl-CoA + glyoxylate + H2O = 3-ethylmalate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: glyoxylate + H2O + pentanoyl-CoA = 3-propylmalate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3-mercapto-2-mercaptomethylpropanoate + NAD+ = asparagusate + H+ + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: N,N-dimethyl-1,4-phenylenediamine + aniline + NADP+ = 4-(dimethylamino)azobenzene + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: O-acetyl-L-serine + zeatin = L-lupinate + acetate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: beta-cyclopiazonate + A = alpha-cyclopiazonate + AH(2).
Catalysis of the reaction: all-trans-geranylgeranyl diphosphate = casbene + diphosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + H2O + oxaloacetate = citrate + CoA, where the acetyl group is added to the re-face of oxaloacetate; acetyl-CoA provides the two carbon atoms of the pro-R carboxymethyl group.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 CoA + NADP+ = CoA-disulfide + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: CoA + glutathione + NADP+ = CoA-glutathione + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: coenzyme F420 + H(2) + H+ = reduced coenzyme F420.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 columbamine + O2 = 2 berberine + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 L-cysteine + NAD+ = L-cystine + H+ + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + lauroyl-CoA + oxaloacetate = (2S,3S)-2-hydroxytridecane-1,2,3-tricarboxylate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + H2O + lauroyl-CoA = (3S,4S)-3-hydroxytetradecane-1,3,4-tricarboxylate + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + phosphoethanolamine = acetaldehyde + NH4 + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: NH3 + NAD+ + H2O = hydroxylamine + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3,4-dihydroxypyridine + O-acetyl-L-serine = 3-(3,4-dihydroxypyridinium-1-yl)-L-alanine + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: phosphoenolpyruvate + N-acetyl-D-mannosamine + H2O = phosphate + N-acetylneuraminate.
Catalysis of the reaction: nitrite + NAD(P)+ + H2O = nitrate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: nitrite + NADP+ + H2O = nitrate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4-(hydroxyamino)quinoline N-oxide + 2 NAD(P)+ + H2O = 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide + 2 NAD(P)H + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-trans,6-trans-farnesyl diphosphate = diphosphate + pentalenene.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-reticuline + O2 = (S)-scoulerine + H2O2 + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: geranyl diphosphate + H2O = diphosphate + sabinene hydrate.
Catalysis of the reaction: trimethylamine + H2O + electron-transferring flavoprotein = dimethylamine + formaldehyde + reduced electron-transferring flavoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction: O3-acetyl-L-serine + uracil = 3-(uracil-1-yl)-L-alanine + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: dihydrozeatin + NADP+ = H+ + NADPH + zeatin.
Catalysis of the reaction: arachidonate + O2 = (5Z,8Z,11Z,13E)-(15S)-15-hydroperoxyicosa-5,8,11,13-tetraenoate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 4-(2-aminoethyl)benzene-1,2-diol + 4-hydroxyphenylacetaldehyde = (S)-norcoclaurine + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + acetylenedicarboxylate = CO2 + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + N6-acyl-L-lysine = L-lysine + a carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-sn-glycerol + O2 + (tetrahydrobiopterin/tetrahydropteridine) = 1-hydroxyalkyl-sn-glycerol + H2O + (dihydrobiopterin/dihydropteridine).
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-3-(4-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-5-yl)propanoic acid + H2O = N-formimidoyl-L-glutamate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-mandelate + 5,6,7,8-tetrahydrobiopterin + O2 = (S)-4-hydroxymandelate + 7,8-dihydrobiopterin + H2O. (S)-2-hydroxy-2-phenylacetate is also known as S-mandelate.
The controlled release of arachidonic acid from a cell or a tissue.

definition.value: This term should be used to annotate release of arachidonic acid from the cell. For the hydrolytic release of arachidonic acid from a phospholipid, consider instead annotating to 'phospholipase A2 activity ; GO:0004623'.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 5'-IMP + H2O = inosine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 5'-GMP + H2O = guanosine + phosphate.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on X-H and Y-H to form an X-Y bond, with a disulfide as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which X-H and Y-H form X-Y and the acceptor is disulfide.
Catalysis of the transfer of a hydroxyl group from one position to another within a single molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl phosphate + H+ + sulfite = phosphate + sulfoacetaldehyde.

definition.value: The reaction occurs in the reverse direction.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + ecdysteroid = UDP + glucosyl-ecdysteroid.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + a 1,4-lactone = a 4-hydroxyacid.
Catalysis of the reaction: NAD+ + sulcatol = H+ + NADH + sulcatone.
Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)+ + sn-glycerol-1-phosphate = NAD(P)H + H+ + dihydroxy-acetone-phosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of an alkylthio group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, with 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, and the other dehydrogenated

value.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from 2-oxoglutarate and one other donor, and the latter donor is dehydrogenated.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on phosphorus or arsenic in donors, with NAD(P)+ as acceptor

value.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a phosphorus- or arsenic-containing group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a NAD(P)+ to NAD(P)H.
Catalysis of the reaction: phosphate + beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine = N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + alpha-D-galactopyranose 1-phosphate.
